  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Regulatory Affairs Pharmacist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>Indrugco Pte Ltd is a distinguished Singapore-based pharmaceutical company committed to operating with integrity alongside our partner principals. Our mission is to provide quality and innovative products, creating significant value for our customers. We believe in fostering a work environment that encourages creativity, entrepreneurial spirit, and the fulfillment that comes from the self-directed expression of talents.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>As a Pharmacist at Indrugco Pte Ltd, you will play a pivotal role in delivering high-quality pharmaceutical services and products by managing wholesale operations, ensuring regulatory compliance, and collaborating with cross-functional teams to drive business growth.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead wholesale operations to ensure full compliance with Singapore’s legal and regulatory requirements, maintaining high standards of good distribution practices</li><li>Oversee and optimize relationships with partner principals and suppliers to ensure seamless supply chain management and product availability</li><li>Monitor and provide expert guidance on clinical information for the company’s portfolio of therapeutic drugs and healthcare supplements to support informed decision-making</li><li>Collaborate with sales and marketing teams to design and execute targeted promotional strategies that enhance product visibility and customer engagement</li><li>Stay current with industry regulations and best practices to proactively address compliance and operational risks</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Pharmacy from an accredited institution</li><li>Registered Pharmacist with the Singapore Pharmacy Board</li><li>Minimum of 2 years of clinical experience</li><li>In-depth knowledge of legal and regulatory requirements in Singapore’s pharmaceutical industry</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Ability to collaborate effectively with sales and marketing teams to support business development initiatives</li></ul><p><br />We also welcome qualified individuals who are actively exploring an extended portfolio in sales and business development in the Singapore pharmaceutical industry, and want to discuss further to apply for the position here at Indrugco Pte Ltd. Join us in contributing to our mission of delivering quality and innovative healthcare solutions.</p>",
